The paper deals with the task of sketch-based image retrieval, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques for cross-domain feature representation learning. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel network architecture that integrates multiple branches and introduces a hybrid-loss mechanism, which involves deep learning and optimization techniques. Hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also focuses on aligning abstract sketches and natural images into a common high-level semantic space, which involves information retrieval and semantic embedding techniques. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper aims to learn more discriminative cross-domain feature representations, which involves artificial intelligence and representation learning techniques. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category.
